news.title: Insolvency & bankruptcy code doesn't give immunity to promoters, directors: SC
news.para: Supreme Court has said the shield of protection under the code is not available to promoters and directors of an insolvent firm and proceedings can be initiated against them.

news.title: Grasim Industries to start paints manufacturing in Dhanansu village of Ludhiana
news.para: The industry has completed the construction of its integrated paint-manufacturing unit at Hi-Tech Valley in Dhanansu village of Ludhiana.

news.title: Ahmedabad development body's plots sale in Bopal draws poor response
news.para: ​Despite hopes of raking in big bucks, Auda managed to secure bids for only two plots, and even these bids exceeded the base price by Rs 100 and Rs 200 per sq m.

news.title: DTCP ramps up checks, demolishes 12 houses in colony off Golf Course Road
news.para: The team comprising assistant town planner, junior engineer and field staff identified 12 under-construction houses that didn’t have a building plan and mandatory approvals.

news.title: Delhi: 161 illegal colonies on O zone making river water toxic
news.para: But 161 colonies in the O zone of the floodplain, with 2.3 lakh households, have been recently identified as unattached to a sewer network. This means that sewage from these areas continues to flow untreated into the river, contaminating its water.

news.title: Gurugram: One-time settlement scheme for EDC dues extended till March end
news.para: The scheme — called Samadhan Se Vikas-2021 — was implemented in 2021 and has been extended multiple times since. The last extension was granted till November 15, 2023.

news.title: Registries to begin in Noida with 1,000 flats first to get green light
news.para: Clearing the decks for this are consent letters from seven real estate companies to clear 25% of their total dues within 60 days and the rest in instalments in line with the relief package rolled out by the state government last month based on recommendations of the Amitabh Kant committee.

news.title: German regulator steps up warnings on property as industry reels
news.para: "Many went overboard in times of extremely low interest rates. That is why a necessary correction has come," Branson told the Finanz-Szene podcast, calling commercial real estate "risk No. 1".

news.title: Sagar Cements posts net loss of Rs 10.18 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Sagar Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 673.14 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 14.09 per cent from Rs 590.02 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: UK: Crest Nicholson's CEO to step down after tough 2023
news.para: RBC Capital Markets analysts said that the challenge for Crest during the transition was to stay focused on execution, adding that a change of management may present an opportunity to adjust strategy.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's net profit up 22.02% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Dalmia Bharat's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 3,664 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 8.05 per cent from Rs 3,391 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Country Garden seeks to sell assets worth $530 million in Guangzhou
news.para: The properties include a hotel resort, four office towers, a shopping mall as well as five rental apartment buildings, according to listings dated Jan. 19 on Guangzhou Enterprises Mergers and Acquisitions Services.

news.title: DLF's net profit up 26.60% in Q3 FY24
news.para: DLF's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,643.51 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 5.38 per cent from Rs 1,559.66 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance's net profit up 25.75% in Q3 FY24
news.para: PNB Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,756 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 2.26 per cent from Rs 1,796.52 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nisus-BCD Fund invests Rs 60 crore in Project High Cliff
news.para: The recent investment in Project High Cliff will be utilised towards the refinancing of existing debt and the timely completion of the project. The luxury project is spread over 1.4 acres of land with a saleable area of around 2.4 lakh sqft.

news.title: SC cancels bail granted to former DHFL promoters
news.para: A bench of Justices Bela M Trivedi and S C Sharma said the high court and the trial court committed error in granting bail to them.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers' net loss widens to Rs 63.04 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 83.70 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 77.65 per cent from Rs 374.46 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: About 20 lakh houses to be built for poor in Jharkhand by 2027: CM
news.para: "Initially, the Centre had accepted that Jharkhand has four lakh poor people. But later, it stated that no poor was left for the central housing scheme in the state. So, we decided to provide houses to eight lakh poor people from the state exchequer," the chief minister said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: 10,000 units sealed for property tax default
news.para: A statement from the civic body said 64 properties in the Central Zone, 243 in the North, 55 in East, 284 in North West and 28 properties in the South West Zones were sealed.

news.title: Ghaziabad: 210 properties sealed, 150 owners rush to clear dues
news.para: The corporation has mopped up Rs 127 crore in taxes this fiscal year. GMC’s chief tax assessment officer Sanjeev Sinha said the corporation had prepared a list of 1 lakh defaulters across the district.
